description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Sister/Charge Nurse to join our busy, friendly Regional Cardiothoracic Critical Care Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint enthusiastic motivated individuals to help lead and support our large nursing team. Candidates must be able to demonstrate their ability to support the management of the unit, manage a team of nurses, support staff within the challenging critical care environment and have knowledge of the multi-faceted NHS. This role requires strong leadership skills to uphold the standards and values of CTCCU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit is the North West Centre for Cardiopulmonary Transplantation. We have an established respiratory ECMO service and as part of our heart failure service the unit is able to provide cardiac ECMO&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit consists of a 31 bedded purpose built Cardiothoracic Critical Care Unit combing both level 2 and level 3 care. As a team we are committed to delivering the highest standard of care. The unit encourages and supports staff development to progress your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Substantial experience within the cardiothoracic critical care speciality, experience in mentoring , education to diploma level, evidence of level 3 studies,ENB100, critical care course and evidence of personal development are expected of all candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is will be subjected to 24hrs internal rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameWendy FawcettJob titleManager CTCCUEmail addresswendy.fawcett@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 291 4531&lt;/p&gt;
